You could mark the `textarea` [form control][1] as `touched` when clicking on the clear button:

    &lt;textarea #txt=&quot;ngModel&quot; [(ngModel)]=&quot;questionText&quot; required ...&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;

    &lt;button (click)=&quot;clear(); txt.control.markAsTouched();&quot; ...&gt;Clear&lt;/button&gt;

See [this stackblitz][2] for a demo.


  [1]: https://angular.io/api/forms/NgModel
  [2]: https://stackblitz.com/edit/angular-mpefsn-yxt4bz?file=app%2Fform-field-theming-example.html

The easiest way would to just use matInput with the textarea

    &lt;mat-form-field&gt;
      &lt;textarea matInput ...&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;
    &lt;/mat-form-field&gt;

then you would have the same style for all the input fields. And material would apply red because it is required.

The harder way, if you want the textarea to be of different style could be to manually add a class to the textarea field.

.ts file:

    public cleared = false;
    ...
    clear() {
      ..
      this.cleared = true;
    }

and in your html:

    &lt;textarea [(ngModel)]=&quot;inputValue&quot; [class.custom_invalid_form_class]=&quot;cleared &amp;&amp; inputValue.length &gt; 0&quot;&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;

The reason you are seeing the red border here for the other fields except for the `textarea` is because the other fields are getting their `CSS` from `.mat-form-field-invalid`. The `.mat-form-field-invalid` gets added to your `mat-form-field` because of this class which gets added when you submit the form without filling the required fields.

So do the same for your `textarea`, remove the `text-error` class as it&#39;s not required and add the `matInput` directive. Then just wrap your `textarea` in a `mat-form-field` like  below
```html
&lt;mat-form-field&gt;
    &lt;textarea matInput name=&quot;questionText&quot; cols=&quot;35&quot; rows=&quot;8&quot; placeholder=&quot;Question Text&quot; [(ngModel)]=&quot;questionText&quot; required&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;
&lt;/mat-form-field&gt;
```

Here is a working example on [StackBlitz][1].


  [1]: https://stackblitz.com/edit/angular-textarea-mat-form-field

